title: Osu playing cards competition slated for October 24
text:
Sports News | 22 October 2015 23:00 CET Osu playing cards competition slated for October 24 By GNA 
Accra, Oct. 22, GNA - This year's Osu playing cards league would take place on Saturday, October 24 at the Blorgodo Gardens Square at Osu. 
It is being sponsored by Mr Sowah Odotei, the Chief Executive Officer of Vallex Lease Company Limited. 
The clubs which will battle for honours in the competition are Five Junction, South Africa, Old Timers, Garden Boys, Akwei Dade Rangers, Odedeshie and Lucky Seven. 
This was disclosed in a statement signed by Nana Nkosua Mingle, the Chairman of the Osu Playing Cards Association, and a copy delivered to the Ghana News Agency. 
GNA
